data.title: TAYLOR SWIFT

data.text:
Taylor Swift is an American singer-songwriter from Nashville, Tennessee. One of the most successful recording artists of the 21st century, Taylor became a pop culture monolith by successfully performing several pivots in genre.

Originally coming to fame as a wunderkind in country, Taylor quickly became known for her confessional, diaristic lyricisms and penchant for a punchy melody.

After three country albums (Taylor Swift, Fearless, Speak Now) made her a homegrown superstar, Taylor's fourth album Red began her experiments with pop, and the beginning of a fruitful partnership with Max Martin, who would executive produce the next two albums to turn Taylor into a galaxy-sized pop star; 1989 and Reputation.

2019's Lover was another full embrace of pop, but it was 2020's surprise lockdown album Folklore which saw Taylor emerge herself into lo-fi indie-core (included too on its sister record, Evermore) which helped her re-establish herself as one of the most talented songwriters of her generation.

An ambitious re-recording of her first seven albums following legal issues, as well as 2022 LP Midnights and the record-setting billion-dollar Eras Tour turned Taylor into the kind of pop culture supernova that we haven't witnessed since Beatlemania. Capping off a remarkable few years in April 2024 with the release of surprise double album The Tortured Poets Department, which defied usual campaign convention to land in the public domain without being preceded by any singles.
